  "description": "The math of relationality — the formal articulation, in standard categorical and bilattice-theoretic vocabulary, of what the relationality framework commits to philosophically. Where relationality cribs its language from philosophy, voidmath cribs from math: predication, fiber algebra, fibration, hyperdoctrine, Priestley duality, sheaf cohomology.",
